task:
Eclipse is open with the workspace at /home/user/workspace.

Create a new Java project 'Calculator' in this workspace (Java nature) with TWO source folders registered on the build path: 'src' and 'test'. Then add the following two source files:

1. src/com/calc/Calculator.java:

```
package com.calc;

public class Calculator {
    public int add(int a, int b) {
        return a + b;
    }

    public int subtract(int a, int b) {
        return a - b;
    }

    public int multiply(int a, int b) {
        return a * b;
    }

    public double divide(int a, int b) {
        if (b == 0) throw new ArithmeticException("Division by zero");
        return (double) a / b;
    }
}
```

2. test/com/calc/CalculatorTest.java:

```
package com.calc;

public class CalculatorTest {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Calculator calc = new Calculator();
        assert calc.add(2, 3) == 5 : "add failed";
        assert calc.subtract(5, 3) == 2 : "subtract failed";
        assert calc.multiply(4, 3) == 12 : "multiply failed";
        System.out.println("All tests passed");
    }
}
```
